# =============================================================
# Should be ignored (add to .gitignore):
# =============================================================

# node_modules — Always ignore, never track.
# *.tgz — Ignore npm pack files.
# build/ — Ignore build output.
# dist — Ignore distribution output.
# *.css, *.min.css, *.purged.css, *.purged.min.css — Ignore compiled/minified/purged CSS.
# *.css.map — Ignore source maps in production (optional, uncomment when ready).
# *.html, **/*.html — Ignore generated HTML files.
# .env, .env.local, .env.development, .env.production, .env.alt — Ignore environment files.
# .vscode/, .idea/, *.sublime-workspace, *.sublime-project — Ignore IDE/editor settings.
# .DS_Store, Thumbs.db, desktop.ini — Ignore OS-specific files.
# *.log, npm-debug.log* — Ignore logs.
# .sass-cache/, .eslintcache — Ignore cache files.
# .husky/_/ — Ignore Husky hooks.
# src/scss/test.scss — Ignore test files.
# notes, docs/temp/ — Ignore dev notes and temp docs.
# CONFIG-JSON-GUIDE.txt, Sass-CLI-Compilation-Guide.txt, package-json-line-by-line-explanation.txt, chat-history*.md, PROBLEMS-FOR-*.md — Ignore dev documentation/notes if not needed in repo.
# certificates, open-laptops.jpg — Ignore large or temporary images.
# contactForm.js, dropdown.js, navigation.js, skillsChart.js — Ignore experimental JS if not ready for production.

# =============================================================
# Should NOT be ignored (do NOT add to .gitignore):
# =============================================================

# package.json, package-lock.json — Always track; these are essential for dependency management.
# Source files you want versioned: main JS, SCSS, HTML templates (e.g., *.template.html), images used in production, documentation you want to share.
# Build/config scripts (unless auto-generated or containing secrets).
# =============================================================
# Special notes:
# =============================================================

# The negation pattern !*.template.html ensures template HTML files are tracked.
# Only ignore dev notes, temp docs, and experimental files if you do not want them in your repo.
# =============================================================
# Summary:
# =============================================================

# Ignore files/folders that are generated, environment-specific, or temporary.
# Track source, config, and documentation files that are essential for your project and collaboration.
# =============================================================


